column5: Does anyone have a link to one? The one I had it seems my internet does not support anymore.

Not sure what you're looking for but here's a few.Topographic MapsOntario MNR Topographic Map MakerDepth MapsAnglers Atlas Trak Maps (you can view maps they sell online)Navionics Web App I am slowly putting maps up on my own site. I don't have many available on there yet, but I will put up whatever map you want that I have access to. Although, Anglers Atlas likely has most of them up already.

Just looking for a site that I can look at a topo map of any given area in Canada. i used to use topo of Canada and worked great but they must have upgraded and my computer will not bring up the info any more. I have Google Earth but haveing elevation lines and such off a topo map is alsi nice.

Gmap4 can display vector topos for all of Canada.Here is a link that opens at Thunder Bay, Ontario.http://www.mappingsupport.com/p/gmap...7261&z=12&t=t5Full disclosure: I am the developer of this browser app. It is a public service and part of my way to "pay it forward". Anyone can use Gmap4 for any non-commercial purpose.The Gmap4 homepage has a FAQ, list of features, examples, quick start info (on the Help page) and more to quickly get you up to speed.Gmap4 default map: http://www.mappingsupport.com/p/gmap4.phpGmap4 homepage: http://www.mappingsupport.com/p/gmap4.htmlJoseph, the Gmap4 guy

Not sure how detailed you need it to be but this is free and has elevation lines.http://www.web2.mnr.gov.on.ca/fish_o...plorer_en.html Pretty awesome resource from the MNR for checking out waters in Ontario.
Joseph - This is an awesome app you developed and thank you for sharing it on this site!
